history.content:
If one were to look on the campus online schedule of classes (see http://schedule.berkeley.edu/srchfall.html ) you would see the following note:

"Enrollment in Fall 2015 for Computer Science 160 will follow the standard enrollment policy for upper-division Computer Science courses (see http://www.eecs.berkeley.edu/Policies/enrollment.shtml#upper). Unlike previous semesters, no applications or petitions will be used. Also, students will be notified of their discussion section assignment on the first day of the lecture. You will not be able to sign up for the discussion section during Tele-BEARS."

See previous responses this evening regarding when we would be able to process waitlists.

children.subject: also, do you think it is likely for me to get in the class now.  Before, if all went as planned when getting off the waitlist, I theoretically would have been admitted. but not it seems to have changed
You are likely looking at old data as your position on the waitlist will have moved by at least 30 students.
Would telebears be showing the old data or schedule.berkeley.edu?
same is happening with me, I've been 55th on the waitlist and haven't moved despite the # of students enrolled increasing

Okay great thanks for the information.  I was wondering if that was the case why people were getting off the waitlist and put into the class, yet my position on the waitlist has barely changed.  Originally I was the 80th spot on the waitlist, and now that about 30 people have been moved off my spot is only 69th.

history.content: Hi, I was wondering when we will know if the waitlist will be admitted into CS 160.  Is there any special action that will need to be taken to get into 160 because I have heard in the past that there was an application process.
